article.headline: Oral Roberts 59, Chicago State 53
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green and Ken Tutt combined to score Oral Roberts' last 15 points over the final eight minutes to help the Golden Eagles outlast Chicago State 59-53 on Thursday night. With 4:14 left, Green sank a free throw that gave Oral Roberts a 48-47 lead it never relinquished. Tutt, who was 5-of-8 from the field, paced Oral Roberts (12-7) with 16 points while Green scored 14. Shawn King contributed 11 points, 11 rebounds and six blocked shots for the Golden Eagles, which won their sixth straight basketball game. David Holston led Chicago State (7-15) with 18 points, but was limited to two in the second half. John Cantrell added 14 points and Kourtney Calvin had 12 rebounds for the Cougars, who led 32-28 at halftime. Moses Ehambe scored seven points in a 3 1/2-minute span, including a 3-pointer that gave Oral Roberts its first lead of the second half at 44-43 with 9:44 left. After Tutt made another 3-pointer, Chicago State tied the game at 47-47 on two free throws by Calvin and a basket by Chidozie Chukwumah. Green's go-ahead free throw began an 8-0 run that was capped by his three-point play that boosted Oral Roberts' lead to 55-47 with 1:56 left. Baskets by Holston and Cantrell cut the Cougars' deficit to 55-51, but Tutt sank 4-of-4 free throws in the final 29 seconds to clinch the win for Oral Roberts, which won after trailing at halftime for the first time this season. It was the first meeting between the teams since Oral Roberts defeated Chicago State in the Mid-Continent Conference tournament championship game last March. Chicago State, now an independent, has lost all 10 games it has ever played at Oral Roberts. The Golden Eagles jumped to a 13-7 lead before Chicago State reeled off a 12-5 spurt, capped by a Cantrell dunk, to go ahead 19-18 midway through the first half. After a Green layup, Chicago State scored seven straight points for a 26-20 advantage. A basket by Cantrell just before halftime gave the Cougars a four-point lead. Holston had 16 points in the first half and made his first three 3-pointers.
